        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for the expression, Polyb., iii., 34, 9. The description of Josephus evidently implies some special occasion, and not the return of the ordinary Quin-quennalia; see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 12:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and also below. Josephus does not menion Blastus, or those of Tyre and Sidon, but this is no reason against the narrative, as Krenkel maintains. Belser, much more reasonably, contends that Luke’s narrative supplements and completes the statement of Josephus.—",
        "children": []
