        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", xix., 8, 2, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "στολὴν ἐνδυσάμενος ἐξ ἀργυρίου πεποιημένην πᾶσαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐσθ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 1:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "βήματος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": Josephus speaks of the event happening in the theatre, and the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "βῆμα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " here = rather “the throne,” R.V. (margin, “judgment-seat”), the royal seat in the theatre from which the king saw the games and made his harangues to the people (so of an orator’s pulpit, ",
